elements.instruction:
if an elastic or ribbing is present anywhere on the garment For each size:
- Stretch the elastic or ribbing and compare the stretched length to the specifications;
- must not have poor recovery

1. Use a strip of pressure sensitive tape (3M 500 for instance) and apply it firmly on the area to be tested: artwork, logo, marking;
2. Press it on the surface so that the tape is properly stuck, with no bubble or wrinkle; 
3. Remove the tape with an angle close to 180 degrees, rapidly but not jerked.
4. Repeat this operation 3 times.

1. Check the workflow of pieces around the metal detection machine;
2. Check the calibration of the metal detection machine;
3. Scan the whole sampling size with the machine.

elements.expectedResult:
- the machine should isolate the packing area from the production line so that 100% of the pieces in the packing line went through the machine;
- The products shall not have any foreign metal objects;
- The calibration should be available and up to date.

